title: The highest-paid female athletes 2019
summary: This grouped bar chart represents Income in million USD on the Y-axis. And, how the value changed throughout 15 Months for Prize money, and Endorsements.
Over the 15 Months, the Income in million USD for both Prize money and Month have decreased.
Out of all 2 groups, Endorsements had the highest Income in million USD in Month Serena Williams (tennis) and Prize money had the lowest Income in million USD in Month P.V. Sindhu (badminton).
In Month Naomi Osaka (tennis), Prize money had the maximum Income in million USD and it saw the lowest in Month P.V. Sindhu (badminton) out of all 15 Months.

max_summary: This is a grouped bar chart showing Income in million USD on the Y-axis throughout 15 Months for Prize money, and Endorsements on the X-axis.
Over the 15 Months, the Income in million USD for both Prize money and Month have decreased.
Out of all 2 groups, Endorsements had the highest Income in million USD in Month Serena Williams (tennis) and Prize money had the lowest Income in million USD in Month P.V. Sindhu (badminton).
Among all the Months, Prize money had the highest Income in million USD in Month Naomi Osaka (tennis) and lowest Income in million USD in Month P.V. Sindhu (badminton).
The maximum Income in million USD for Prize money that was found in Month Naomi Osaka (tennis) was 16.6 times larger than the minimum Income in million USD observed in Month P.V. Sindhu (badminton).
Among the groups, Prize money had the biggest difference in Income in million USD. Where the maximum Income in million USD was 16.6 times larger than the minimum Income in million USD.

On average, the Month Serena Williams (tennis) had the highest Income in million USD for all 2 groups Prize money, and Endorsements. Whereas Ariya Jutanugarn (golf) had the lowest average Income in million USD.
